 Chelsea manager Thomas Tuchel has two injury worries ahead of his first London Derby against Tottenham Hotspurs on Thursday night. German tactician will be hoping Kurt Zouma and Kai Havertz are able to play a part against Jose Mourinho’s Spurs despite both players off the training pitch with little issues.  Tuchel begins his reign with Chelsea with a goalless draw against Wolverhampton Wanderers at Stamford Bridge last Wednesday before his victory in the 2-0 win over Burnley. According to Football London, Chelsea manager Tuchel has named a 25-man squad to tackle Spurs at the Tottenham Hotspur Stadium. Goalkeepers: Edouard Mendy, Kepa Arrizabalaga and Willy Caballero. Defenders: Reece James, Cesar Azpilicueta, Antonio Rudiger, Thiago Silva, Kurt Zouma (if fit), Andreas Christensen, Ben Chilwell, Marcos Alonso and Emerson Palmieri. Midfielders: Hakim Ziyech, Callum Hudson-Odoi, Jorginho, N’Golo Kante, Mateo Kovacic, Billy Gilmour, Mason Mount, Kai Havertz (if fit), Faustino Anjori and Christian Pulisic. Strikers: Tammy Abraham, Timo Werner and Olivier Giroud. Tuchel will be looking to help the Blues to record a second successive Premier League win over Jose Mourinho’s Spurs maintain his unbeaten start to life at Stamford Bridge. Post Views: 
